label: AB11CD3_cP16_221_a_dg_b_c-001
title: Model of Ferrite Structure (cP16)
comments: Ferritic steels are alloys of iron and other metals with an averaged body-centered cubic structure. This model represents one approximation for a ferritic steel. It is not meant to represent a real steel, and the selection of atom types for each Wyckoff position is arbitrary. When $x_{5}=1/4$ all the atoms are on sites of a bcc lattice.
